definition.value: A branched amino tetrasaccharide consisting of an N-acetyl-alpha-L-fucosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galacturonosaminyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-L-quinovosamine trisaccharide unit, the galacturonosaminyl residue of which carries also an N-acetyl-alpha-L-rhamnosaminyl residue via a (1->4) glycosidic linkage. Corresponds to the tetrasaccharide repeating unit of the capsular polysaccharide of Vibrio vulnificus BO62316.
An L-alpha-amino acid zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of methylmercury L-cysteine; major species at pH 7.3.
